      "span_text": "A n increased level of angiotensin-II (AngII), as is found in heart failure, is associated with an increased risk of ventricular tachycardia (VT), and treatment with angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors and angiotensin receptor blockers reduces that risk.  Investigating the mechanisms of AngIIinduced arrhythmia may result in finding new antiarrhythmic targets."
    },
