      "citation_id": "[CITATION_2]",
      "span_text": "We demonstrated that homozygous mice (ACE8/8) have a high rate of sudden cardiac death (SCD), with telemetry monitoring showing that ≈80% of the SCD resulted from VT and less commonly severe bradycardia and conduction block, in the absence of any left ventricular structural or functional abnormality at the studied age.  The VT and bradycardia were the result of c-Src tyrosine kinase activation, connexin43 (Cx43) reduction, and the impairment of gap junction conduction."
